<div {{ attributes }} >
    <div class="pb-5" style="background-color: {{ NeoxDashSetup.theme|default('#ffffff') }}" >
        <div class=" sticky-top" >
            <turbo-frame id="NeoxDashHeader" >
                <twig:NeoxDashHeader :NeoxDashSetup="NeoxDashSetup" id="live-NeoxDashHeader" />
            </turbo-frame >
            {#    {% include '@NeoxDashBoardBundle/_Partials/header/Inc-Header.html.twig' %} #}
        </div >
        <div class="container" >
            {#    <div class="accordion" id="accordionExample"> #}
            <div id="NeoxDashBoardContent" >
                {% if NeoxDashSetup.class is not empty %}
                    {% for class in  NeoxDashSetup.class %}
                        <turbo-frame id="NeoxDashBoardContent-{{ class.id }}" >
                            <twig:NeoxDashBoardContent :NeoxDashClass="class" :loopn="loop" id="live-NeoxDashBoardContent@{{ class.id }}" />
                        </turbo-frame >
                    {% endfor %}
                {% else %}
                    <h1>Hello Neox DashBoard BUNDLE ! ðŸ¤ª ðŸ¦– ðŸ¦– ðŸ¦–</h1>
                    <p>
                        This project aims to offer users a streamlined and efficient solution for integrating a dashboard into their website. Designed with ease of use and speed in mind, it simplifies the process of
                        creating customizable and dynamic dashboards, enabling users to quickly access and manage important data on their platforms. Whether for monitoring metrics, visualizing performance, or organizing
                        key information, this solution provides a user-friendly approach to implementing dashboards in a fast and intuitive way.

                        <span style="font-weight: bold; color: tomato">All are not finsh !!! it's still on beta version.</span>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        1 - Edit the Navigation Bar :
                        <button {{ stimulus_controller('@xorgxx/neox-dashboard-bundle/neox-modal', {
                            title: 'Configuration dash board' ,
                            text: 'Do you want to continue' ,
                            idElement: "live-NeoxDashHeader",
                            url: path('app_neox_dash_setup_edit', { id: NeoxDashSetup.id })

                        }) }}
                            data-modal="modal"
                            data-action="click->xorgxx--neox-dashboard-bundle--neox-modal#modal"
                            class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"
                            type="button"
                        >
                            <twig:ux:icon class="flex-shrink-0 icon-normal me-2" name="fa6-solid:user-gear" width="20" style="height: auto;" />
                            Menu...
                        </button >
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        2 - Add a Minimum of One Content Element :
                        <button {{ stimulus_controller('@xorgxx/neox-dashboard-bundle/neox-modal', {
                            title: 'Add Content' ,
                            text: 'Do you want to continue' ,
                            idElement: path('app_neox_dashboard'),
                            url: path('app_neox_dash_class_new', { id: NeoxDashSetup.id })

                        }) }}
                            data-modal="modal"
                            data-action="click->xorgxx--neox-dashboard-bundle--neox-modal#modal"
                            class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"
                        >
                            <twig:ux:icon class="flex-shrink-0 icon-normal me-2" name="fa6-solid:folder-plus" width="20" style="height: auto;" />
                            Add Content ...
                        </button >
                    </p>
                    <div class="">
                        <h4 class="my-3">
                            Usage in future
                        </h4>
                        <div class="border-bottom mb-3 text-dark"></div> <!-- Ligne horizontale -->
                        <p>
                            In the future you will having to click on main menu : <twig:ux:icon class="flex-shrink-0 icon-normal" name="fa6-solid:sliders" width="30" style="height: auto;" color="black" />

                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        <h4>In conclusion ðŸŽ‰</h4> have fun exploring and implementing these features! Whether you're building a dynamic dashboard or enhancing user interactions with modals, the possibilities are endless. Enjoy the
                        process, experiment with new ideas, and let your creativity shine. Happy coding!
                    </p>
                {% endif %}
            </div >

            {#    </div> #}
        </div >
    </div >
</div >





